Three people were killed and two wounded in a mass shooting in Maryland, U.S. on Thursday, days after a deadly mass shooting at a Texas elementary school. As the U.S. is still embroiled in partisan debates, the inaction on gun control is splitting the country's roots, finally becoming a severe threat to public safety. Editor: Yuan Xin Chief editor: Ge Jing Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)